{"type":"text","timestamp":1773437518674,"sessionID":"ses_316e48f3cffeGrhJEXdprD247G","part":{"id":"prt_ce91c8ade0019xDrctUj2n3doX","sessionID":"ses_316e48f3cffeGrhJEXdprD247G","messageID":"msg_ce91c7fdb001n95q3mi60LFtp6","type":"text","text":"## Goal\n\nImplement per-feature agent type selection for the wombo-combo orchestration system. This means adding an `agent` field to the task YAML schema so each task can specify which agent definition file (from `.opencode/agents/`) to use, instead of always using the default `generalist-agent`. Also add an `--agent` CLI flag to the launch command.\n\n## Instructions\n\n- Add an `agent` field to the task YAML schema in `src/lib/task-schema.ts`\n- Add an `--agent` flag to the launch command\n- When launching, use the specified agent type instead of the default `generalist-agent`\n- The `agent` field should be **optional** — when omitted, default to `generalist-agent.md`\n- When set, it should reference an agent definition file name (**without extension**) from `.opencode/agents/`\n- Update `renderAgentTemplate()` in `src/lib/templates.ts` to accept an agent name parameter\n- Use conventional commits with scope `agent-selection-per-feature`\n- Commit after each logical unit of work\n- Do NOT push to remote or modify `tasks`\n- Run `bun run build` to verify everything works at the end\n- Use `portless run` when starting any server\n- Use `bun dev` not the global binary when testing\n\n## Discoveries\n\n1. **`agent_type` already exists** on the `Task` interface in `src/lib/tasks.ts` (line 88) — this is for the **external registry** (e.g., `engineering/engineering-frontend-developer` from GitHub). The new `agent` field is **different**: it references a **local** agent definition file from `.opencode/agents/`.\n\n2. **`agent-registry.ts`** handles the existing `agent_type` → external registry flow. The new `agent` field is for **local** agent definitions, which is a simpler/separate mechanism.\n\n3. **`renderAgentTemplate()`** in `templates.ts` (line 333-338) currently just delegates to `renderGeneralistAgent()` with no agent name parameter. It needs to be updated to accept an optional agent name and render the appropriate template.\n\n4. **`ensureAgentDefinition()`** in `templates.ts` (line 353) checks for `.opencode/agents/{config.agent.name}.md` and reinstalls from the generalist template if missing. This may need updating to handle per-task agents.\n\n5. **`LaunchOptions`** in `launcher.ts` already has an `agentName?: string` field that gets passed to `--agent` flag when spawning the opencode process.\n\n6. **`AgentState`** in `state.ts` already has `agent_name: string | null` and `agent_type: string | null` fields.\n\n7. **`task-store.ts`** has a `normalizeTask()` function (line 219) that cleans up null/empty `agent_type` values — the same pattern should be applied for the new `agent` field.\n\n8. **`LaunchCommandOptions`** in `launch.ts` does NOT currently have an `--agent` flag — it needs to be added.\n\n9. The **`_meta.yml` template** documents the task schema and should be updated with the new `agent` field.\n\n10. **`CLIArgs`** in `index.ts` needs an `agent` field, and the arg parser needs a `--agent` case.\n\n## Accomplished\n\n- **Completed**: Full codebase exploration and analysis of all relevant files\n- **Completed**: Created a TODO plan with 8 items\n- **Not started**: No code changes have been made yet\n\n### TODO items (all pending):\n1. Add `agent` field to Task interface in `src/lib/tasks.ts`\n2. Update `task-schema.ts` to validate the `agent` field\n3. Update `task-store.ts` to handle the `agent` field serialization\n4. Update `renderAgentTemplate()` in `templates.ts` to accept an agent name parameter\n5. Add `--agent` flag to CLI args in `index.ts` and pass to launch command\n6. Update `LaunchCommandOptions` and `launch.ts` to use per-task `agent` field\n7. Update `templates/_meta.yml` to document the `agent` field\n8. Run typecheck and build, fix any errors\n\n## Relevant files / directories\n\n### Core files to modify:\n- `src/lib/tasks.ts` — Task interface (add `agent?: string` field, line 65-89)\n- `src/lib/task-schema.ts` — Schema validation (add validation for `agent` field)\n- `src/lib/task-store.ts` — Task serialization/normalization (line 219-232, `normalizeTask()`)\n- `src/lib/templates.ts` — `renderAgentTemplate()` (line 333-338), `ensureAgentDefinition()` (line 353-385)\n- `src/commands/launch.ts` — `LaunchCommandOptions` (line 115-136), `cmdLaunch()` (line 1355), `launchSingleHeadless()` (line 192)\n- `src/index.ts` — `CLIArgs` (line 117-168), `parseArgs()` (line 212-392), help text (line 398-513), launch case (line 687-711)\n- `src/templates/_meta.yml` — Task schema documentation (line 37)\n\n### Files for reference (already read, no changes needed):\n- `src/config.ts` — WomboConfig type, `DEFAULT_CONFIG` (agent.name defaults to \"generalist-agent\")\n- `src/lib/agent-registry.ts` — Existing external agent registry (separate from local `agent` field)\n- `src/lib/launcher.ts` — `LaunchOptions.agentName` already exists (line 51)\n- `src/lib/state.ts` — `AgentState.agent_name` already exists (line 59)\n- `src/lib/prompt.ts` — Prompt generation (no changes needed)\n- `.opencode/agents/generalist-agent.md` — Default agent definition\n- `AGENTS.md` — Development guidelines\n- `package.json` — Build scripts (`bun run build`)","time":{"start":1773437518673,"end":1773437518673}}}
