{"type":"text","timestamp":1773437762635,"sessionID":"ses_316e48f3cffeGrhJEXdprD247G","part":{"id":"prt_ce920b04c001cskHKXYISi35iZ","sessionID":"ses_316e48f3cffeGrhJEXdprD247G","messageID":"msg_ce920a718001bYBaPtj0STNo25","type":"text","text":"The `launchSingleHeadless` already handles writing specialized agents from the registry. When using a local `agent` field, the agent definition already exists in `.opencode/agents/` in the main project — and since worktrees share the git repo, the `.opencode/` directory should be available. But let me check how `writeAgentToWorktree` works and whether the worktree has access to `.opencode/agents/`:","time":{"start":1773437762634,"end":1773437762634}}}
